  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The AfriKids Street and Working Child Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In northern Ghana life is balanced on a knife edge. The country is stable and developing, for every child a good education and safe, comfortable life is within reach. But for those on the wrong side of that knife edge life can quickly spiral out of control; life on the streets or in child labour is tough and addictive, and mainstream education can be difficult to access and reintegrate with. The AfriKids Street and Working Children Programme will target children who are out of education because they either live on the streets or work in illegal forms of labour. It will work with the children, their carers and the government to get them back into education and to address the root causes of their problems so that once the course of their life is changed, it is changed for good.</narrative>
  </description>
